---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout-en.astro';
---

<Layout 
	title="About Adorable – AI Consulting and Paid Social"
	description="Adorable is a consultancy for AI consulting and paid social. Over 10 years helping companies with digital marketing and AI transformation."
	swedishPath="/om"
>
	<main>
		<section class="hero">
			<div class="container">
				<h1 class="hero-title">About Adorable</h1>
				<p class="hero-intro">
					A consultancy for companies that need senior expertise in paid social and AI consulting without hiring full-time.
				</p>
			</div>
		</section>

		<section class="section">
			<div class="container">
				<h2 class="section-title">Background</h2>
				<p class="text">
					Adorable was founded in 2016 and has over 10 years of experience in digital marketing. The focus started with paid social – Meta Ads, LinkedIn, TikTok, YouTube – helping companies actually get a return on their ad spend.
				</p>
				<p class="text">
					In 2023, AI became a core part of the offering. Not because it was trendy, but because of what it could do. Today Adorable helps organizations go from AI-curious to actual implementation.
				</p>
			</div>
		</section>

		<section class="section">
			<div class="container">
				<h2 class="section-title">How Adorable works</h2>
				<p class="text">
					Adorable works with a select few clients at a time, usually when things are a bit unclear. Most of the work happens close to the business – finding the right direction, raising quality, and helping teams make better decisions before they become expensive.
				</p>
				<p class="text">
					The goal is to be close enough to be useful, do the work when it helps, and step back when the team has it covered.
				</p>
			</div>
		</section>

		<section class="section">
			<div class="container">
				<h2 class="section-title">Clients</h2>
				<p class="text">
					Creative agencies, tech companies, construction firms, insurance companies, education businesses and more. Adorable works with both B2B and B2C companies. What they have in common is that they need senior expertise – but not a full-time hire.
				</p>
				<p class="text">
					Often it's companies in a growth phase where the right expertise at the right time makes a difference. Sometimes it's established companies that need new expertise for a specific project.
				</p>
			</div>
		</section>

